3.Change the double quotation marks in the WHERE clause expression to single quotation marks. 
3.WHERE句の式のダブルクォーテーションをシングルクォーテーションに変更します。


%let State=NC;
%let CreditMin=700;
proc sql;
create table Customer&State as
select CustomerID, Employed, Race, 
       Married, State, CreditScore
    from sq.customer
    where State=”&State” and
          CreditScore > &CreditMin;
quit; 

↓

%let State=NC;
%let CreditMin=700;
proc sql;
create table Customer&State as
select CustomerID, Employed, Race, 
       Married, State, CreditScore
    from sq.customer
    where State='&State' and
          CreditScore > &CreditMin;
quit; 


Run the query. 
クエリーを実行します。

How many rows are in the new table?  Note: Type a numeric value.
新しいテーブルには何行ありますか？ 注：数値を入力してください。

正解
Zero rows are returned. The macro variable doesn't resolve inside of single quotation marks. 
Instead, the WHERE clause is searching for the character string '&State'.  



